result.execSummary:
The defendant Alexis A Martinez was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case. One or more other charges in this case were dismissed. The dismissed charges were not proven and have no legal effect. Alexis A Martinez is presumed innocent of the dismissed charges.

  • Alexis A Martinez was found guilty of Resisting or Obstructing an Officer, a class A misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 946.41(1).

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Alexis A Martinez in court with attorney Thomas K. Hackbart.  Defendant Alexis A Martinez in custody.  Student Intern Carlos Pedraza under the supervision of Randy P. Sitzberger for Hanna Kolberg appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  BRANCH 22 FOR BRANCH 35.  Case in court for jury trial, however parties would like to proceed with a plea hearing instead.
Pursuant to plea negotiations Count 8 is DISMISSED.  As to Count 7:    Defendant changes his plea to GUILTY.  Defendant examined as to his plea, advised of his Constitutional rights and the maximum penalty.   Defendant advised that if not a United States Citizen, deportation is possible.  Court found that defendant knowingly, voluntarily and intelligently waived his rights.  Guilty Plea Questionnaire/Waiver of Rights and Addendum received and filed.  Parties stipulate to the complaint as a factual basis to sustain defendant's plea.  Court found defendant guilty and ordered a Judgment of Conviction be entered on the record.  Case adjourned for sentencing in Branch 35.  Sentencing hearing scheduled for January 5, 2016 at 08:30 am.
